insert  into `news`(`news_id`,`title`,`content`,`date`,`author`,`abstractContent`,`photo`) values (16,'WKU Research Shown at the 33rd Annual ACM Human Computer Interaction Conference','ACM CHI conference is an annual premier conference on computer human interaction organized by ACM SIGCHI and sponsored by large companies and NSF\r\n\r\nCHI is the premier international forum for human-computer interaction. This year, the conference attracted more than 2900 researchers from around the world to exchange their latest research in advancing Human-Computer and Human-Robot interactions.\r\n\r\nOur poster (second from the left), along with posters by researchers from University of Basel and MIT; many other posters are from world-class universities such as Carnegie-Mellon Univ., Harvard, Stanford, Univ. Michigan, Univ. British Columbia, Univ. College London, Univ. Edinburgh, Univ. Stuttgart, TU München, RWTH Aachen, KU Leuven, TU Delft, Univ. Tokyo, Tsinghua Univ., NUS, KAIST, among others.\r\n\r\nDuring the conference, they presented their system “Having Fun Over a Distance: Supporting Multiplayer Online Ball Passing Using Multiple Sets of Kinect” side by side with one from MIT (Massachusetts Institute of Technology) Artificial Intelligence Lab and another two from University of Basel (one of the leading universities in Switzerland); many other students from such top universities as Harvard University, Stanford University, Carnegie Mellon University, Princeton University, Northwestern University, Cornell University, Georgia Institute of Technology, National University of Singapore, University of Tokyo, also showed their works there.\r\n\r\nThe demonstrated system made use of three sets of Microsoft Kinect to construct an augmented virtual ball passing game that allows multi-players to interact with each other over a distance. Meanwhile, it also allows users to be able to see each other in person and the environment.\r\n\r\nThe system at a glance\r\n\r\nThe system demo can be watched at: Having Fun Over a Distance: Supporting Multiplayer Online Ball Passing using Multiple Sets of Kinect\r\n\r\nThe paper documenting this research can be downloaded from the ACM Digital Library at: Having Fun Over a Distance: Supporting Multiplayer Online Ball Passing Using Multiple Sets of Kinect\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, the WKU team also presented their work in the Third International Symposium of Chinese CHI (Chinese CHI 2015) during April 18-19, 2015. Chinese CHI is Chinese leading forum for research in all areas of Human-Computer Interaction. It attracts an international community of practitioners, researchers, academics and students from a wide range of disciplines including user experience design, software engineering, human factors, information systems, social science and creative industries among other disciplines. Other speakers presented their papers in the venue come from National Taiwan University, University of Michigan, Tsinghua University, Peking University, etc.\r\n\r\nDr. Tang, Dr. Winoto and Yongfu (Relic) would also like to acknowledge the support from Wenzhou-Kean University, especially the Academic Affair Office. Many thanks also go to Stellar Shi from the Academic Affairs office for her numerous helps and kindness.','2015-04-30','Jessie','During April 18 to 23, 2015, Computer Science professor Dr. Tiffany Y. Tang, Dr. Pinata Winoto and junior student Yongfu (Relic) Wang attended the 33rd Annual ACM Conference on Human Factors in Computing (ACM CHI 2015) in Seoul, Korea.','NewsImg/2e8ff170-d8aa-4a2f-b433-0448d37178f6.png'),(20,'Microsoft Imagine Cup 2016','Good News: Microsoft Imagine Cup 2016\r\n\r\nThe Computer Science Department is thrilled to announce that a team of two freshmen supervised by Dr. Pinata Winoto has won the third prize in the annual Microsoft Imagine Cup 2016 (World Citizenship category) in China, after two rounds of fierce competition from teams from other top Chinese universities. The two freshmen are Odd Aonan Guan and Will Fangzhou Ye. The team, W0!, developed a collaborative puzzle game with both tablet and large-screen tabletop versions to train children with autism joint attention skills.\r\n\r\nMicrosoft Imagine Cup is the world’s premier student technology competition. Since the first Imagine Cup in 2003, there are 1.65 million students from more than 190 countries and regions participated in the competition. Till 2015, there are more than 100,000 Chinese students participated in Imagine Cup which has been dubbed as the “Programming Cup” in China and has had a huge influence on Chinese IT and Internet industries.\r\n\r\nWe would like to use this opportunity to acknowledge the generous financial support from Wenzhou-Kean University and the Office of Research and Sponsored Program (ORSP); thanks also go to Aries Yuanbo Huang (AAO) and Elena Xiangxiang Zhu (ORSP) for their supports and helps.','2016-04-12','Jessie','The Computer Science Department is thrilled to announce that a team of two freshmen supervised by Dr. Pinata Winoto has won the third prize in the annual Microsoft Imagine Cup 2016 (World Citizenship category) in China.','NewsImg/bcd2f478-b12a-4955-b446-eb8c875f0fce.png'),(21,'1st Prize, Microsoft ImagineCup 2017 China Final','We are developing a highly customizable spatial memory training mobile application for individuals with mild cognitive impairment or dementia. The application comes with two paired modes as Caregiver mode and Patient mode. With an intuitive touch-based system spatial information training mechanism, each item that is important for day-to-day activities are paired with mirroring visual tags in real life with those in the application. Through touch-based interactive technology, speech recognition, image tagging via Microsoft Cognitive Services and voice-enabled search technology, the application offers an enjoyable and intuitive user experience. \r\n\r\nAdditionally, through cloud-based (MS Azure) behavioral modeling and remote data sharing, it can enable personalized spaced repetition memory learning and offer real-time behavioral data for the medical specialist and care-givers.','2017-06-19','Jessie','MeTAP: A Highly Customizable Spatial Memory Training Application for individuals with Mild Cognitive Impairments and Dementia (1st Prize, Microsoft ImagineCup 2017 China Final)','NewsImg/b6f9fbfd-cee7-4c2c-8fb9-d420a0c1a3f7.png'),(22,'The Microsoft Kinect National Competition','Under the supervision of Dr. Tang, four students in two teams participated in the Second Kinect National Competition beginning September 2013; the competition required participants to design and build a FIFA World Cup themed Microsoft Kinect project. Around 150 projects were submitted for the competition overall, and after defeating teams from other leading universities including Peking University, Chinese University of Science and Technology, Nanjing University, Shanghai Jiaotong University, Zhejiang University in China, both teams entered the final after hosted in Shandong University from May 10 to May 11, 2014, where one of the teams snatched third place.\r\n\r\nThis is our first attempt and first-win. Congratulations to all students for their continuing hard-works during the eight month: Relic Yongfu Wang, Candice Yuan Chen, Will Yicheng Wang, Youyu Hui!','2014-09-09','Jessie','Under the supervision of Dr. Tang, four students in two teams participated in the Second Kinect National Competition beginning September 2013; the competition required participants to design and build a FIFA World Cup themed Microsoft Kinect project. ','NewsImg/77c394ba-6d99-4a38-9dd1-946a2e01d60a.png'),(23,'The Hackathon','From April 18 to April 20 nine Computer Science undergraduate students, accompanied by two CS faculty, Drs. Winoto and Tang, participated in the 2014 Microsoft Kinect for Windows All-Night Hackathon and won second and third place. In 24 hours they and other software developers, undergraduate, and graduate students developed software products for Microsoft’s Kinect v2, and at the end of the hackathon their products were evaluated by a panel of Microsoft judges. Drs. Winoto and Tang also enjoyed the opportunity to attend a Microsoft-held workshop on their latest Kinect product immediately preceding the hackathon.','2016-04-08','Jessie','From April 18 to April 20 nine Computer Science undergraduate students, accompanied by two CS faculty, Drs. Winoto and Tang, participated in the 2014 Microsoft Kinect for Windows All-Night Hackathon and won second and third place.','NewsImg/f48a94e9-a31c-44a1-823c-33f9dd74e312.png'),(24,'CST Meeting with Vice Chanellor Eric Yang','President Yang first shared the interesting stories he experienced while studying in the United States. His Ph.D. major was molecular cell biology, but he took a lot of computer courses by himself, and finally got a master\'s degree in computer science. He said that many courses in computer science require a lot of work, and he also said that he understands the hard work of computer students. He felt a lot of pressure while studying with graduate students from well-known universities such as Tsinghua, Peking University, Jiaotong University and other computer science classes, and spent a lot of sleepless nights to complete his degree in computer science. He confessed that he had found that all four major questions had no ideas in an important examination of the most challenging algorithm course, and if this compulsory algorithm course, which is only offered once a year, failed, he would lose his full scholarship. \r\n\r\nAnd postpone one year. This also means that he will interrupt his study and life in the United States, and he stood up nervously and wanted to give up the exam. But when he saw that those academic masters who came from a class had been stubbornly insisting, he said to himself, \"I can do what others can do.\" It is this kind of thinking that has always encouraged him, and in the end he got the same results as those of Tsinghua and Peking University in his class.\r\n\r\nThat was the only one of his grades that was not an A when he was studying in the United States for a master\'s and doctoral degree, but it was the subject he learned the most, grew the most, and mastered the most knowledge. He said that \"only through difficulties and setbacks can we truly grow.\" There are some difficulties in front of you that you find it difficult to overcome, but after passing through these difficult times and breaking through the siege under pressure, you will find that the baptism of this difficult time is the most precious wealth of future career and life. President Yang said frankly that his study path and scientific research work during his Ph.D. study were not all smooth sailing. There were many setbacks and failures in the experiment, but he always maintained an optimistic attitude and perseverance. \"Destiny will make fun of you. If you are wrong, you will be wrong, and you will start over if you are wrong.\" Such a mentality is even more a kind of courage and confidence to challenge difficulties.\r\n\r\nSecondly, President Yang also introduced several buildings under construction by Winken. Several plans have been designed for the comprehensive laboratory building. What difficulties have been encountered during the construction process? The reason for the long construction period is our excellence in the design and quality of the building. He shared them one by one with his classmates, and he has an affinity.\r\n\r\nFinally, he kept reminding students not to slacken their studies. In particular, students in the computer science department must not indulge in games. Adults are responsible for their actions and future prospects. Another important issue is to observe academic integrity, which is the point that every professor constantly emphasizes. I believe that the students must have new insights after attending this meeting with the principals, and they will also have more positive motivation to face the heavy academic pressure. I wish every student can achieve ideal results in the exam week, \"You don\'t make a donation. You are good.\"','2020-09-19','Zimeng Yu','On the evening of September 29th, WKU’s “net celebrity” Eric Yang, President Yang, shared a lot of his study abroad experience with the students of the Polytechnic Institute at CBPM C135 and the students put forward some suggestions on study and life.','NewsImg/ea5ecb29-a786-485f-88a8-535d9b3bbab4.png'),(25,'On this express train to the field of big data, WKUers get on the train!','At 9:00 am, the Semir Hall of the Business School was full of seats. The big data innovation seminar is held here. Dr. Yang Yixin, vice president of our school, said that this year marks the tenth anniversary of Wenken\'s school. There are 140 full-time teachers and more than 2,900 students. This year, Winken has opened one doctoral program and five master programs, and will recruit more than 100 graduate students.\r\n\r\n\r\nHe said that with the rapid development of the big data industry, the demand for big data talents will inevitably continue to increase. Winken\'s mathematics course focuses on applied mathematics and data analysis. These students are highly competitive in employment in emerging fields such as digital information and big data analysis. He believes that this conference will strengthen cooperation between academia and industry, enhance exchanges in the new development of the big data industry, and help realize the common mission of serving Wenzhou\'s technology and talent needs.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn the seminar, Sun Cheng, the general manager of Djeman Technology Co., Ltd., firstly gave a speech on \"Djeman Big Data Project Development Direction and Case Analysis\". Starting from the general trend of digital reform, Sun Cheng interpreted the development direction of Zhejiang Province\'s vigorous development of \"Digital Zhejiang\", and introduced the main research and development directions of DJM, including the construction of smart parks, smart transportation, and smart folks.\r\n\r\n\r\nSubsequently, Chen Jiyu of Zhejiang Huawei Intelligent Technology Co., Ltd. took \"Huawei Intelligent Big Data Application Practice-Problem Thinking and Future Prospects\" as the topic, and interpreted the trend of digital development by introducing Huawei\'s digital project. Huawei Intelligent is deeply involved in the field of smart housing and construction information, focusing on the integration of big data, the Internet of Things platform and financial service platform and other specific applications, such as smart parking service platform, corporate salary payment supervision platform, etc. In the report, he pointed out that the development of big data is also facing issues such as the legality and compliance of digitization, and the safe use of personal information. Finally, he hopes to carry out more in-depth school-enterprise cooperation with Winken, give full play to their respective advantages, and solve the problems in the development and application of big data; the two sides jointly build innovative pilot projects, and Huaneng is also very willing to provide internship and visit opportunities for Wenken students. Provide support for college entrepreneurial teams.\r\n\r\nFinally, Professor Zhuang Xihai, assistant to the dean, researcher, and doctoral supervisor of the School of Big Data of Fudan University, brought a report on the topic of \"Medical Image Analysis and Application\". Professor Zhuang\'s main research direction is medical imaging and image processing, big data and artificial intelligence algorithms, etc. He mainly introduced the concept and algorithm of medical imaging, as well as the application direction in medicine.\r\n\r\nAt the same time as the seminar, the big data innovation job fair is also underway in the lobby area on the first floor of the Business School.\r\n\r\nZhejiang Huawei Intelligent Technology Co., Ltd., Dejieman Technology Co., Ltd., Wenzhou Zhongjin Advanced Technology Research Institute, Zhejiang Chuangli Electronics Co., Ltd., New H3C Group, China Telecom Wenzhou Branch and other technology companies came to Wenzhou with their own shortages. Ken, in order to find outstanding talents in the field of big data.\r\n\r\nThe reporter saw at the scene that the recruitment positions are rich, including network pre-sales engineers, JAVA engineers, WEB development engineers, technical support, database engineers, sales, operation and maintenance implementation engineers, etc.\r\n\r\nIn just two hours, the Zhongjin Research Institute received more than 10 resumes. Ms. Zheng, the person in charge of the company\'s personnel department, said that the Zhongjin Research Institute and Winken have always maintained a school-enterprise partnership. Currently, Wenken graduates are employed in the institute. She is very affirmed of the abilities and work attitude of Winken students. Many senior students majoring in mathematics and mathematics application from Winken came for the post of data analyst.','2021-03-21','Shu Wang','Today, the Wenzhou-Kean University Enterprise Data Innovation Seminar and a special job fair co-organized by the Research Office of our school, the School of Science and Technology, and the Career Development Center was held in the School of Business.','NewsImg/58e83d34-b8a5-45d0-b644-998ca7b796c9.png'),(26,'Student Research Day: Invite you to unlock the mysteries of research!','Want to get involved in scientific research, don’t know how to take the first step? The 6th Student Research Day of Wenzhou-Kean University will provide you with an exploration platform and escort your scientific research road. The registration time for this event will close at 4 pm on March 15th.\r\n\r\nAs an annual scientific research feast, WKU Student Research Day has been dedicated to stimulating students\' academic potential and enthusiasm for scientific research, and cultivating students\' critical thinking ability, innovation ability, teamwork ability, social practice ability, etc. This student academic research day continues the past tradition and is divided into three parts: poster presentation, keynote speech and three-minute speech. The school will finally select the first, second, and third prizes based on the results, and the winners will receive the equivalent prizes and certificates of 3,000 yuan, 2,000 yuan and 1,000 yuan respectively.','2021-03-11','Shenlan Lou','Want to get involved in scientific research, don’t know how to take the first step? The 6th Student Research Day of Wenzhou-Kean University will provide you with an exploration platform and escort your scientific research road. The registration time for this event will close at 4 pm on March 15th.','NewsImg/ceaf0ce5-b197-4013-8366-172c058f9690.png'),(27,'WKU Computer Information System (Master of Science)','Professional presentation\r\nWenzhou-Kean University\'s Computer Information System (Master of Science) major aims to train students to become leaders in the field of information technology, and can engage in work in commerce, government, banking, industry, e-sports and other fields. Students can have an in-depth understanding of different aspects of the field, and learn how to design, build and maintain complex systems, and master the current related cutting-edge technologies. At the same time, the major encourages students to work closely with teachers for more in-depth work and research. Professional courses include: computer information systems, advanced analysis algorithms, database systems, software engineering, software assurance, digital forensics and investigations, website design and development, human-computer interaction, knowledge discovery and data mining, interactive information visualization, advanced artificial intelligence , Machine learning innovation, etc. Graduates can engage in software engineering, information technology system development, network security, artificial intelligence, machine learning, security monitoring and other related jobs.\r\n\r\nAdmission requirements and related application materials\r\nBachelor\'s degree certificate in computer science (or related field)\r\n*Students who graduated from non-U.S. colleges and universities need to take NACES certification (https://www.naces.org), and choose World Education Services (WES) certification (course-by-course certification is required).\r\n\r\nOfficial transcripts of all learning stages above high school (excluding high school). The cumulative grade point average (GPA) is not less than 3.0 (applicants below 3.0 will be considered based on the situation).\r\nTwo letters of recommendation\r\nresume\r\nPersonal statement\r\nWhen necessary, the department will arrange an interview\r\nOfficial score report of TOEFL, IELTS or Duolingo within two years\r\n*TOEFL iBT 79 points, paper-based 550 points, IELTS 6.5 points, Duolingo 100 points.','2020-08-31','Author','Wenzhou-Kean University\'s Computer Information System (Master of Science) major aims to train students to become leaders in the field of information technology, and can engage in work in commerce, government, banking, industry, e-sports and other fields. Students can have an in-depth understanding of different aspects of the field, and learn how to design, build and maintain complex systems, and master the current related cutting-edge technologies.','NewsImg/9441786e-dbfe-4958-9371-54fc2403345c.png'),(28,'ISCC Lecture - Computer Network','On the evening of March 26, the research center WKU Institute of societal and contemporary computing (ISCC) where Professor Dr. Sujatha Krishnamoorthy and Professor Dr. Ken Ehimwenma of the Department of Computer Science and Technology of the Wenzhou-Kean University College of Technology invited Dr Kennedy, a PhD professor at the University of Sheffield, UK Offor explained the difficulties of online computer network knowledge.\r\n\r\nThis course was started by Dr. Ken Ehimwenma, who briefly reviewed the basic knowledge system of Networking, including the application layer, transport layer, network layer, data link layer, and physical layer computer layered network introduction in computer networks and The respective functions have given all the participants a clearer understanding of computer network architecture. Immediately afterwards, Dr. Ken further elaborated on the definition and principle of message tracking in the computer network for message transmission, and led to the following demonstration practice by Professor Kennedy on the use of Cisco network visualization software.\r\n\r\nIn the Cisco demonstration, Professor Dr Kennedy Offor first started with the home device terminal, and gradually built the necessary elements in many network devices including routers, ISPs, and so on, and built it into a simple but complete computer simulation network. Using this network, the professor completed the answers to the problems of delay and packet loss in the process of packet transmission, as well as the demonstration of the whole process of message transmission, and used examples to vividly show the details of the TCP three-way handshake, so that the students have a better understanding of the computer network. A clearer and comprehensive understanding.\r\n\r\nAfter the lecture, the students actively participated in the questioning of the content of this class, and the atmosphere was lively, and the professor also explained his questions in a comprehensive and logical language. At the end of the class, Professor Dr. Sujatha Krishnamoorthy and Professor Dr. Ken Ehimwenma expressed their gratitude to Dr. Kennedy Offor for the wonderful lecture on behalf of ISCC and affirmed the active participation of the students. At the same time, Professor Dr. Sujatha said that he will continue to offer such lecture courses in the future, so as to make students have a more comprehensive understanding of the computer network system.','2021-03-25','Aska Hou Yueran','On the evening of March 26, Professor Dr. Sujatha Krishnamoorthy and Professor Dr. Ken Ehimwenma of the Department of Computer Science and Technology of Wenzhou-Kean University invited the British Xie Dr Kennedy Offor, Ph.D. Professor of Field University, explained the difficulties of online computer network knowledge.','NewsImg/ba0e7eeb-06d1-4581-93b0-957d268b5240.png');

