nin City, Dimaf Graphics Print.\r\n\r\nEhimwenma, E. K. & Agbator, O. L. (2006). Data Processing and the Fundamentals of Computing. Benin City, Dimaf Graphics Print.','Multi-agents planning, Deep neural nets','Ken E. Ehimwenma, Ph.D. Computer Science; M.A. Information Communication Technology & Education; B.Sc.Ed. (Hon) Compute Science; N.C.E. Physics & Chemistry. Dr Ehimwenma completed his Ph.D. at the Sheffield Hallam University United Kingdom with specialty in multiagent systems, knowledge representation, and computational logic. \r\n\r\nDr Ehimwenma has a number of publications in many refereed journals and conference proceedings, and he is a member of several Program Technical Committee and Peer Reviewer to many conference events. \r\n\r\nDr Ehimwenma lives with his family in England and work at the Kean University (Wenzhou Campus). Dr Ehimwenma like indoor exercise, outdoor walking, and listening to classical music. One thing that he would like to do next is learn to play the piano.\r\n\r\nEmail: kehimwen@kean.edu\r\n\r\nOffice: GEH C421'),(20,'Baha Ihnaini, Lecturer','ProfImg/1a757a6f-9919-4ea8-b1f9-eac1c9aaddd4.png','Computer Operating Systems  Fundamental of Computer Science  Microcomputer Applications','Sep 2014 – Oct 2019\r\nD. in Computer Science\r\nUniversity Utara Malaysia (UUM), Malaysia\r\n\r\nSep 2006 – Jul 2008\r\nS. in MIS\r\nThe Arab Academy for Banking and Financial Sciences, Jordan\r\n\r\nSep 2000 – Jul 2005\r\nS. in Computer Engineering\r\nPhiladelphia University, Jordan','Ihnaini, B., & Mahmuddin, M. (2020). Valence Shifter Rules for Arabic Sentiment Analysis, International Journal of Multi-disciplinary Sciences and Advanced Technology, 1 (2), 167-184.\r\n\r\nIhnaini, B., & Mahmuddin, M. (2020). Phonology Matching Algorithm to Construct Palestinian Sentiment Lexicon, International Journal of Multidisciplinary Sciences and Advanced Technology, 1 (3), 35-51.\r\n\r\nIhnaini, B., & Mahmuddin, M. (2018). Lexicon-Based Sentiment Analysis of Arabic 