aches the Microcomputer Applications (CPS1032) course at WKU which is a class for students to learn about Microsoft Office application software.\r\n\r\n Professor Yee enjoys teaching the students at WKU and instilling them with computer skills that they can apply towards their achievement at WKU, as well as, into their future careers.\r\n\r\nEmail: jyee@kean.edu\r\n\r\nOFFICE: GEH B406'),(22,'Yongfu Wang Relic, Lecturer','ProfImg/a34bb766-4de4-4042-b8bb-7f2c8041ff89.png','CPS 1231 Fundamentals of Computer Science  CPS 2231 Computer Organization & Programming  CPS 3740 Database Management Systems  TECH 2920 Computer Systems','Kean University (Union, NJ), Wenzhou (Wenzhou-Kean University, WKU)\r\nBachelor of Science in Computer Science (BS), Minor in Mathematical Science, May 2016\r\n\r\nNorthwestern University (Evanston, IL), Master of Science in Computer Science (MS), December 2017','My recent research focuses on human-computer interaction (HCI), affective computing, ubiquitous computing, and applications of sensing and wearable technologies especially on autistic children. I joined Autism Research Network founded by Dr. Tiffany Tang since 2015. I am interested in utilizing current emerging HCI technology and theory to assist autistic children in China and evaluate how could these technology and theory benefit this group.','Computer Science','I am a lecturer in the department of Computer Science at Wenzhou Kean University. I received my master’s degree in computer science from Northwestern University. Received my bachelor’s degree in computer science and minor in Mathematical Science from Wenzhou-Kean University. \r\n\r\nMy recent research focuses on human-computer interaction (HCI), affective computing, ubiquitous computing, and applications of sensing and wearable technologies especially on autistic children.\r\n\r\nEmail: yongfuw@wku.edu.cn\r\n\r\nOFFICE: GEH C421'),(23,'Muhammad Shoaib, Lecturer','ProfImg/087b5a02-06a6-4927-88ba-ef33e56271ef.png','Systems Simula